# Angular Features

## Service pattern

```typescript
@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })
export class ItemsService {
  private readonly supabase = inject(SupabaseService).client;
  private readonly _items = signal<Item[]>([]);
  private readonly _loading = signal(false);
  readonly items = this._items.asReadonly();
  readonly loading = this._loading.asReadonly();

  async load(): Promise<void> { /* supabase.from(...).select() */ }
}
```

## Page pattern

- `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`
- Inject service, expose readonly signals
- `ngOnInit` calls `service.load()`
- Never inject `SupabaseService` in pages

## Routes

```typescript
export const ITEMS_ROUTES: Routes = [
  { path: '', loadComponent: () => import('./items.page').then(m => m.ItemsPage) },
];
```

Register in `app.routes.ts` with `loadChildren` + guards.

## Filters

Use `signal('')` + `computed()` — plain properties break OnPush reactivity.
